name: 23S rRNA (adenine2030-N6)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine2030 in 23S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N6-methyladenine2030 in 23S rRNA
comment: The recombinant RlmJ protein is most active in methylating deproteinized 23S ribosomal subunit, and does not methylate the completely assembled 50S subunits [1].

references.title: The last rRNA methyltransferase of E. coli revealed: the yhiR gene encodes adenine-N6 methyltransferase specific for modification of A2030 of 23S ribosomal RNA.
